Dependency=Bedrooms: # Source: Constructed using 5-yr 2017 Public Use Microdata Samples (PUMS).IPUMS USA, University of Minnesota, www.ipums.org.
# Assumption: The number of occupants per unit is limited to 10. At 10 occupants the CDF is greater than 99%.
# Assumption: Where sample counts are less than 10, the state average distribution (for the relevant number of bedrooms and building type) has been inserted.
# Assumption: Mobile homes in DC are replaced with distributions from Single-Family Detached (for relevant number of bedrooms) in DC.
# Assumption: Rhode Island 1 bedroom Single-Family Attached distributions are replaced with the state average Rhode Island 2 bedroom Single-Family Attached distributions.
